The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) has warned resident of Zamfara, Sokoto, Kebbi and Kano states to be weary of a pending flood. This is coming just as NEMA Sokoto Operations office embark on sensitization and awareness campaign to ensure adequate emergency preparedness, mitigation and response to flood disaster. The Director General, NEMA, AVM Muhammad Alhaji Mohammed who was represented by the Head of Planning, Research and Forecasting Unit, Tukur Abubakar, stated that the agency is taking bold steps to tackle the impending likely flood incidents that may occur as predicted by  NIMET. Meanwhile, the Coordinator, National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA), in Kano Territorial Office, Alhaji Sanusi Ado, has said that 20 Local Government Areas in Kano State are classified under high risk of flooding in 2020.